6. Most Common Product Combinations

Business Question:Which products are often bought together?

```sql
SELECT 
    oi1.product_id AS product_1,
    oi2.product_id AS product_2,
    COUNT(*) AS times_bought_together
FROM order_items oi1
JOIN order_items oi2
ON oi1.order_id = oi2.order_id
AND oi1.product_id < oi2.product_id
GROUP BY product_1, product_2
ORDER BY times_bought_together DESC;
```

Insight:
Product 1 and 4 are the most successful crosspair with 3,142 joint purchases.

Business Recommendation:
Immediately implement a "frequently bought together" checkout bundle for these two items to further increase the multi order rate.



7. Conversion Funnel Analysis

Business Question:** Where do users drop off in the website funnel?

SQL QUERY
SELECT
    COUNT(DISTINCT ws.website_session_id) AS sessions,
    COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN wp.pageview_url = '/products' 
    THEN ws.website_session_id END) AS product_page,
    COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN wp.pageview_url = '/cart' 
    THEN ws.website_session_id END) AS cart_page,
    COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN wp.pageview_url = '/shipping' 
    THEN ws.website_session_id END) AS shipping_page,
    COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN wp.pageview_url = '/billing' 
    THEN ws.website_session_id END) AS billing_page,
    COUNT(DISTINCT o.order_id) AS orders
FROM website_sessions ws
LEFT JOIN website_pageviews wp
ON ws.website_session_id = wp.website_session_id
LEFT JOIN orders o
ON ws.website_session_id = o.website_session_id;


Insight:
The conversion funnel shows a massive drop_off at the Biling page (only 3,617 reached to 64,484 on the shipping page), indicating a technical bug or a friction point in the checkout process that is preventing customers from completing their 32,313 intended orders.

Business Recommendation:
Conduct an immediate UI/UX audit an dtechnical "bug hunt" on the billing page to fix the broken checkout flow, as resolving this could potentially increase your completed orders by 10X based on the interest shown at earlier stages.



